%% Graph-RAG retrieval vs single-hop grep.
flowchart LR
  classDef seed fill:#ecfeff,stroke:#0891b2,color:#0f172a
  classDef hop fill:#eff6ff,stroke:#1d4ed8,color:#0f172a
  classDef rank fill:#fffbeb,stroke:#d97706,color:#451a03
  classDef out fill:#f0fdf4,stroke:#16a34a,color:#052e16

  Q["Natural-language query\n'who validates JWTs?'"]:::seed
  Q --> S["1. Dense vector seed\nembed query -> top-k symbols"]:::seed
  S --> H["2. Multi-hop BFS\nexpand CALLS / REFS / IMPORTS"]:::hop
  H --> PR["3. Relevance prune\nkeep high-signal nodes"]:::hop
  PR --> RK["4. Rank with distance decay\n(hop distance weights)"]:::rank
  RK --> CTX["5. Build context\nsignatures + skeletons\n(fits token budget)"]:::out
  CTX --> LLM["Feed LLM\nprecise, minimal context"]:::out

  Q -.->|"baseline: grep"| GRP["single-hop keyword match\nno dependencies\nno semantic recall"]:::hop
